narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Lots of reading, lots of writing, lots of class discussion, not a lot of grammar in class but be prepared to see it later on tests. You will get better at French from taking this class, that's for sure. I would definitely recommend the class.
This is a genuinely fun and useful composition course. I would recommend it in a heartbeat. The readings are also interesting and literary.

I would recommend this class to any advanced student since it is a good combination of grammar review and interesting discussion which help to improve conversation/writing skills at an academic level.
A good way to solidify and practice French. I would absolutely recommend it

This was a really intense but incredibly rewarding course! I really feel like I have a grasp of the language and can speak somewhat comfortably in conversation. Its strength was a great grasp of the language and a comprehensive overview of grammar. Also intensive conversation practice and HUGE amounts of writing in French. A weakness would be overkill with the amount of writing assigned. It was overwhelming and in some ways counterproductive after a point because I couldn't focus on it as intensively as I would have it I had fewer writing assignments.
